OL,6,FThe government at the time predicted
OL,7,Fsavings of #1.4 billion a year ` but
OL,8,Factually achieved just #100 million.
OL,10,FThat was under the coalition
OL,11,Fgovernment, but the OBR was also the
OL,12,Fproblem for the Tories' recent attempt
OL,13,Fto reform welfare.
OL,15,FMinisters claimed it was all about
OL,16,Fincentivising work (and not cutting
OL,17,Fmoney) but the OBR assessment told a
OL,18,Fdifferent story.
