OL,6,FIt claimed that while over 400,000
OL,7,Fpeople would see their benefits cut,
OL,8,Fonly around 15,000 would move into
OL,9,Fwork.
OL,11,FSo, the OBR has a history of being
OL,12,Fsceptical about savings from changing
OL,13,Fbenefit threshold rules, and the
OL,14,Fpositive impact of employment
OL,15,Fincentives.
OL,17,FFor the Tories, it meant that a legal
OL,18,Fchallenge was heard and won `
